couldn't necessarily prove

00:09:15.660 --> 00:09:17.980
that it was moonshine
instead of water.

00:09:17.980 --> 00:09:19.990
You could sit there all day and
argue that it was water.

00:09:19.990 --> 00:09:21.560
And he would say no,
it's moonshine.

00:09:21.560 --> 00:09:23.670
So what he would do is he would
take some of the liquid

00:09:23.670 --> 00:09:24.180
in question.

00:09:24.180 --> 00:09:27.640
He would put it in a little
spoon, and light it.

00:09:27.640 --> 00:09:33.080
Now, as it happens, a mixture of
alcohol and water will burn

00:09:33.080 --> 00:09:38.150
as long as there is at least 50%
alcohol in that mixture.

00:09:38.150 --> 00:09:39.360
So he would light it.

00:09:39.360 --> 00:09:42.330
If it lit, he would tax you.

00:09:42.330 --> 00:09:44.820
Because it was at least
50% alcohol.

00:09:44.820 --> 00:09:50.710
And the phrase became, 50%
alcohol, 100% proven that it

00:09:50.710 --> 00:09:52.040
was taxable.

00:09:52.040 --> 00:09:52.280
OK?

00:09:52.280 --> 00:09:53.970
So that's where that
comes from.

00:09:53.970 --> 00:09:55.870
And that way you'll always kind
of remember the math.

00:09:55.870 --> 00:09:59.840
So cut the proof in half,
and you get the ABV.

